\date{2024-12-04}
\title{abelian groups as #{\ZZ}-modules}
\taxon{connection}
\author{rileyshahar}

\import{macros01}

\p{Since [#{\ZZ} is the initial ring](rs-00BC), there is a unique ring
homomorphism from #{\ZZ} to [#{\End(A)}](rs-00B7) for any [abelian
group](rs-007Y) #{A}. This defines an [isomorphism](rs-0002) of
[categories](rs-002V) [\scat{Ab}](rs-00B1) #{\cong} #{\ZZ}\scat{Mod}.}


